extbackslashov         erline\{n\}\_gas/n\_cri)\^\{0.91\}, for gas at solar         metallicity, while for metallicity Z \&lt; 0.1 Z$_{☉}$, based on         our limited sample, f$_{*}$ is reduced by a factor of         {\ensuremath{\sim}}5. (iv) The most compact and massive clouds         appear to form globular cluster progenitors, in the sense that         star clusters remain gravitationally bound after the gas has         been expelled.},
