suremath{\approx}} 0.4-0.7 in the far-UV (1500 {\r{A}}), the         LyC (900 {\r{A}}), and at the Lyman edge (912 {\r{A}}). These         ratios can be used to calibrate the LyC escape fractions in         starbursts.},
