math{\lambda}}{\ensuremath{\lambda}}4959,5007 +         H{\ensuremath{\beta}}) recently observed at z≃ 7.5\{--\}8.5 is         similar to what is observed in this galaxy. Only the James Webb         Space Telescope will measure optical line ratios at         z\textbackslashgt 7, allowing a direct comparison with the         lower-redshift LyC emitters, such as that reported here. <P         />Based on observations made with the NASA/ESA Hubble Space         Telescope, obtained at the Space Telescope Science Institute,         which is operated by the Association of Universities for         Research in Astronomy, Inc., under NASA contract NAS 5-26555.         These observations are associated with programs 9425, 11359,         12060, 12440, 14088.},
