. This also explains the observed relation of         accretion rate and stellar mass, dot\{M\} {\ensuremath{\propto}}         M\_star$^{1.8}$. The efficiency required to convert infall         motion into turbulence is a few percent in all three cases. <BR         /> Conclusions: We conclude that accretion-driven turbulence is         a universal concept with far-reaching implications for a wide         range of astrophysical objects.},
